{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the law to allow an individual to have a pets ashes buried with them",
        "additional_details": "There are many people who only have their pets and no family and want their pets (family) to remain with them after death.  It is just as heartbreaking losing a loved pet to some, as it is to lose a family member and I believe there would be no threat to the environment to allow this.\r\nThose who have never had a partner or children can look to a pet as the only love they ever had and I believe it would give them a greater peace of mind if they knew they would always be together.",
        "background": "The current law prevents individuals from having a beloved pet's ashes buried with them.   I believe the law should be changed to allow this",
